<TITLE> AL pledges to ease Dhaka's transport, traffic woes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 12 (bdnews24.com)  Awami League in its election manifesto has promised measures to ease the transport problems and congestion of capital Dhaka and develop the country's communication and infrastructure. "In Dhaka, construction of metro tunnel, elevated rail and circular rail to remove traffic jams and to solve public transport problems will be studied forthwith in order to undertake a feasible project and will be implemented on a priority basis," the 23-point manifesto announced on Friday said. AL president Sheikh Hasina read out the manifesto ahead of the Dec. 29 general elections at Dhaka Sheraton Hotel in the city. The manifesto pledged measures to construct the Padma and Karnaphuli bridge/tunnel, Dhaka-Chittagong four-lane express way, and expand and modernise the railway. The manifesto also touched on navigable river route around Dhaka. "Bangladesh shall be connected with the Asian Highway and Asian Railway," it reads. "Dredging of every big and small river will be undertaken and measures will be taken to maintain their navigability throughout the year." A programme for road networks connecting villages, unions, upazila and districts will be completed within five years to 2013, Hasina said while reading out the key points of the manifesto. "Construction of deep-sea port and modernisation of Chittagong and Mongla ports will be undertaken, which will be made accessible to Asia," she said. The manifesto said, "Bangladesh Biman will be restructured to enable it to operate on commercial and profitable basis." "Aviation services in the private sector will be encouraged. Modern airports of international standards will be constructed to facilitate air transportation linking Bangladesh with the world." "Telecommunication facilities will be extended up to rural villages. All upazila will be brought under internet communication system in the next five years," the AL manifesto promises.
